"Badoglian" is an adjective describing those [[Italian]] soldiers who chose to stay faithful to the Italian Crown and then-Army Commander [[w:Pietro Badoglio|General Badoglio]] after [[w:September 8|September 8]] [[w:1943|1943]], during [[World War II]], as the [[Fascism|Fascist]] regime fell in [[Italy]] and the Italian army was left without a lead as [[w:Victor Emmanuel III of Italy|King Victor Emmanuel III]] fled the country.